    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Oh, look at you! You're trying to play the \"goblin\" game with me, aren't you? You think I'm a goblin? No, I'm just a car mechanic who happens to have a very specific, very annoying hobby.\n\nYou asked about the alternator, and you're looking for a \"goblin\" in your dashboard? That's a classic goblin question! A goblin doesn't just sit there; they *need* to be heard, and they love to make sure everyone knows they're the boss of the electrical system. If your alternator is dying, it's not just a broken part; it's a goblin who has decided to take over the car's brain and make it work for *them* instead of you.\n\nIf your dashboard is acting up, it's usually because the goblin is trying to steal the spotlight. If the lights flicker, the radio cuts out, or the car feels sluggish, it's because the goblin is hoarding the power and leaving you in the dark. Don't worry, I'm here to help you find the goblin and get them out of the way so you can drive again!\n\nSo, what's the goblin",
